New Records: Ben Stokes scored 108 runs, passing 10,000 international runs across all formats
Key Match Events: England scored 339 for 9, Netherlands scored 179 all out
Post-Match Reflections: England moved off the bottom of the World Cup table, now ahead of the bottom three on net run-rate
Miscellaneous Highlights: England's talisman Ben Stokes fired to help post the target
Others: England's captain Jos Buttler looked increasingly bereft
Dutch were 179 all out in 37.2 overs, despite two drops from an England side
